>>394444
>I'll try my hand at animating something in the meanwhile and post the results

if you have any questions, feel free to ask.

to make a gif in gimp/gnu-imp it basically goes like this:

drag and drop an image of yours into the main window, then drag additional images into the "Layers, Channels, Paths, Undo - Gradients" window. finally, you get to do FOUR SAVES!!!!! fantastic huh?

> "File"
> "Save as..."
> add .gif at the end of the filename in "Name" (it doesn't do it automatically)
> open the arrow down/up menu and select "GIF image (*.gif)"
> "Save"
> select "Save as Animation" (keep "Convert to Indexed..")
> "Export"
> "Save"
